[16:12:43.819564]   Root-cause history (see research note 2026-04-11_crossval12):
[16:12:43.819566]    • Before the ground-plane fix, rfx used `pec_faces={"z_lo"}`
[16:12:43.819567]      to get a free z-boundary PEC. That turned the entire domain
[16:12:43.819577]      floor into an infinite PEC sheet — a cavity, not an antenna —
[16:12:43.819578]      and shifted the resonance 8 % high (2.618 vs 2.424 GHz).
[16:12:43.819580]    • Before the PML fix, OpenEMS used `MUR` at ≈λ/4 margin which
[16:12:43.819581]      reflected energy and made the effective cavity larger,
[16:12:43.819583]      shifting the resonance 8 % low (2.231 vs 2.424 GHz).
[16:12:43.819584]    • The two bugs pointed in opposite directions and gave a 17 %
[16:12:43.819586]      inter-tool gap. With both fixed (rfx = explicit finite PEC box
[16:12:43.819587]      BELOW substrate; OpenEMS = PML_8 + 50 mm margin) the gap is
[16:12:43.819588]      under 1 %.
[16:12:43.819590] 
[16:12:43.819591]   NOTES:
[16:12:43.819593]    • Reference tool is OpenEMS (not Meep) because it is the
[16:12:43.819594]      canonical open-source patch-antenna reference.
[16:12:43.819596]    • rfx single-cell lumped-port S11 dip is shallow (~2 dB) because
[16:12:43.819597]      the single-cell port has parasitic reactance — use Harminv for
[16:12:43.819598]      the clean resonance frequency, the S11 dip only as a
[16:12:43.819600]      passivity / local-dip confirmation.
